================================================================
extract downloaded zip file --> extracted folder paste into your eclipse workspace
===============================================================

open eclipse with your workspace

file--> import --> maven --> existing maven project -->next --> 
root directory --> browse (downloaded file 14.8 kb folder)
-->pom.xml file (automatticall shown)
-->finish

problems --> 1 error
	jdk 22 is not available in your system.

fix the problem:
project name --> build path -->configure build path --> libraries
	-->jre system library 
	--> double click
	--> alternate jre: installed jre button click-->add-->standard jvm -->next -->directory button click -->
	c:/program files/java/jdk22  select
	jre system libraries jar file added automattically.
	finish button click --> 
	installed jre's --> tick latest 22
	apply 
	alternate jre : jdk-22 select.
	finish
	apply , apply and close.
	
problems error fixed
======================================
suppose you faced pom.xml file error --> cvc-elt.1.a: Cannot find the declaration of element 'project'
change all http into https in first two line in pom.xml file (3 places)
========================================
project structure:
==================
pom.xml (important file - maven configuration file) project version & dependencies
help.md ---->project information
src/main/java/...your package ---> filename.java file (First Entry point -- spring boot application starting point)
src/main/resource.........> application.properties --> (configuration process about database....)
                 -----> static folder -->css images javascript file
			     ------>template folder -->html file tempate
every file contains -----> model view controller repositary services
use of mvc ----->code management easily
running project:
================
controller -->simple javascript file
controller use --> api request management from clinet (browser)
src/main/java-->com.yourproject.yourpackage-->right click -->class -->name: TestController -->finish
program:
package com.yourproject.yourpackage;
@RestController (user add --> annotation)
public class TestController
{
@GetMapping("/test")
public String test()
{
	return "HELLO WORLD";
}
}
note: ctrl+shift+o (automattically adding annotation headers..)

your mainfileappliation.java --> right click -->run as -->java application
							-->we will see error to add db configuration
src/main/resource -->application.properties --> spring.autoconfigure.exclude=org.springframework.boot.autoconfigure.jdbc.DataSourceAutoConfiguration
run or play button
tomcat server running port 8080
goto browser : http://localhost:8080/test
you can see output












